Subject: Add support for delays in a level expression.

Full_Name: Chris Myers
Version: 
OS: 
source: 
log: 
Submission from: han.elen.utah.edu (155.99.23.196)
Submitted by: myers


It may be useful to be able to specify delays within a level expression.
e.g. [a<1,3> & b<2,4>]; c+

In this case, c would rise after 1 to 3 times if caused by a and 2 to 4 if
caused by b.

This will require a change to the language syntax, loader, rule data
structure, and timing analysis.

